## Acquire and configure the ID token

After you grant the proper role to the calling service account, follow these
steps:

1. Fetch a Google-signed
[ID token](https://docs.cloud.google.com/docs/authentication/token-types#identity-tokens) by using one
of the methods described in the following section. Set the audience claim
(`aud`) to the URL of the receiving service or a configured [custom audience](https://docs.cloud.google.com/run/docs/configuring/custom-audiences).
If you are not using a custom audience, the `aud` value must remain as the
URL of the service, even when making requests to a [specific traffic\\
tag](https://docs.cloud.google.com/run/docs/rollouts-rollbacks-traffic-migration#tags).

2. Add the ID token you fetched from the previous step into one of the following
headers in the request to the receiving service:

   - An `Authorization: Bearer ID_TOKEN` header.
   - An `X-Serverless-Authorization: Bearer ID_TOKEN` header. You can use this
     header if your application already uses the `Authorization` header for custom
     authorization. This removes the signature before passing the token to the user
     container.

For other ways to get an ID token that are not described on this page, see
[Methods for getting an ID token](https://docs.cloud.google.com/docs/authentication/get-id-token#methods).

### Use the authentication libraries

One way to acquire and configure the ID token process
is to use the authentication libraries.
This code works in **any environment**, even outside of Google Cloud,
where the libraries can obtain authentication credentials for a service
account. To use this method, you
[download a service account key file](https://docs.cloud.google.com/iam/docs/keys-create-delete#creating), and
set the environment variable `GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS` to the path of the
service account key file. For more information, see
[service account key](https://docs.cloud.google.com/docs/authentication/set-up-adc-on-premises#wlif-key).

This code does not accept authentication credentials
for a [user account](https://docs.cloud.google.com/docs/authentication#user-accounts).

[Node.js](https://docs.cloud.google.com/run/docs/authenticating/service-to-service#node.js)[Python](https://docs.cloud.google.com/run/docs/authenticating/service-to-service#python)[Go](https://docs.cloud.google.com/run/docs/authenticating/service-to-service#go)[Java](https://docs.cloud.google.com/run/docs/authenticating/service-to-service#java)More

